{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1769619674,"nonce":"vv38Meolb2bxuqqVUg/nbTtPIS8=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87mdPfg","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/99","origin":"github"},"title":"Add workspace validation tool to verify repos match configuration","message":"## Problem\n\nWe have tools to validate `.repos` file syntax and sync existing repositories, but no tool to verify that the actual workspace matches the configuration:\n\n- ✅ **validate_repos.py**: Validates `.repos` YAML syntax\n- ✅ **sync_repos.py**: Pulls updates for existing repos\n- ❌ **No tool to check**: Are all configured repos actually cloned?\n\n## Current Gap\n\nWhen asked \"are all layers up-to-date with configs?\", there's no simple command to run. Manual comparison reveals:\n\n```\nRepository Configuration vs Actual Workspace Comparison\n============================================================\nConfigured repos: 21\nActual repos: 18\n\n❌ In config but MISSING from workspace (3):\n   - seafloor_echoboat_project11\n   - unh_echoboats_project11\n   - unh_marine_simulation\n```\n\n## User Impact\n\n- **Setup issues go undetected**: Missing repos only discovered when builds fail\n- **Manual validation required**: No `make validate-workspace` or similar\n- **Inconsistent state**: Workspace can drift from configs without detection\n\n## Proposed Solution\n\nCreate `.agent/scripts/validate_workspace.py`:\n\n```python\n#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nValidate workspace matches .repos configuration.\n\nChecks:\n1. All repos in configs are cloned\n2. All cloned repos are in configs (detect orphans)\n3. Repos are on expected branches/versions\n\"\"\"\n```\n\n**Features**:\n- Compare actual workspace against each layer's `.repos` file\n- Report missing repos (should be cloned)\n- Report extra repos (orphaned, not in config)\n- Report version mismatches (wrong branch/commit)\n- Support `--fix` to auto-import missing repos\n- Exit code for CI integration\n\n**Integration**:\n1. Add `make validate` Makefile target\n2. Add to `health_check.sh`\n3. Document in CLI_COMMANDS.md as `/validate-workspace`\n4. Add to AI_CLI_QUICKSTART.md setup checklist\n\n## Example Usage\n\n```bash\n# Check workspace status\nmake validate\n# or\npython3 .agent/scripts/validate_workspace.py\n\n# Auto-fix by importing missing repos\npython3 .agent/scripts/validate_workspace.py --fix\n```\n\n## Related\n\n- `.agent/scripts/validate_repos.py` - Validates syntax only\n- `.agent/scripts/sync_repos.py` - Syncs existing repos only\n- vcstool doesn't provide cross-layer validation\n\n---\n**🤖 Authored-By**: `Copilot CLI Agent`","files":null}]}